message.content: cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.LG. The paper discusses the Bibliometric-enhanced Information Retrieval (BIR) workshop series, which focuses on information retrieval and bibliometrics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also mentions scientific corpora and studies on how scientific knowledge is created, communicated, and used, which could fall under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper may touch on topics related to social media and network analysis, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
